# Energetic-minima alternatives (§14.17, Q11) -- three SPLM variants
# probing the free $V_{\theta}$ head: (i) LayerNorm-after-step, (ii) weak
# scale-gauge penalty on $V(\xi_0, h_0)^2$, and (iii) Gaussian-mixture
# head. Each variant ships training log + loss curve + checkpoint; the
# comparison_{report.md,table.json} and the four-variant landscape grid
# synthesise the cross-cut.
notebooks/conservative_arch/energetic_minima/results/*.pt filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
notebooks/conservative_arch/energetic_minima/results/*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
notebooks/conservative_arch/energetic_minima/results/*.jsonl filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
notebooks/conservative_arch/energetic_minima/results/*.json filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Multi-seed sweeps (E1 onward, §15.16) -- N=5 (or N=3) per architecture
# under a single tag. Each tag directory ships top-level curated +
# auto-generated reports (E1_report.md, E1_shakespeare_report.md,
# E1_shakespeare_divergence_diagnostic.{png,md}, three
# E1_shakespeare_loss_curves_<arch>.png overlays, run_log.jsonl,
# _phase_transition.log) plus per-seed subdirectories
# <arch>/seed_<k>/ containing the checkpoint (~28 MB each), training
# log, summary, loss curve, and stdout/stderr capture. With 13 seeds
# at E1, total LFS payload is ~370 MB; recursive `**` patterns cover
# all current and future tags.
notebooks/conservative_arch/multi_seed/results/**/*.pt filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
notebooks/conservative_arch/multi_seed/results/**/*.pkl filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
